    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Sonoma County and Napa Valley wines?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Sonoma County wines tend to be more diverse and food-friendly than Napa Valley, with cooler coastal influences creating more elegant, restrained styles. While Napa focuses heavily on Cabernet Sauvignon, Sonoma excels across multiple varietals including Pinot Noir, Chardonnay, and Zinfandel. Sonoma also offers significantly better value, with exceptional wines available at 30-50% less than comparable Napa bottles.</p>
